<head>
<title>Alexis de Tocqueville Institution Overview</title>
</head>
<body text="#000000" link="#0000ff" vlink="#551a8b" alink="#ff0000" bgcolor="#ffffff">
<a href="index.htm">
<p><img src="http://www.schoolreport.com/AdTI/education/files/redhome.gif" align="bottom" BORDER="0" ALT="See File" ></a><img src="http://www.schoolreport.com/AdTI/education/files/adtimed.gif" align="bottom" >
<h1 align="center"><font color="#800080"><strong>The Alexis de Tocqueville Institution</font></strong></h1>
<h3 align="center"><em><font color="#800080"><u>The People of AdTI</font></em></u></h3>

<p align="center"><em><u>Executive Chairman</u></em>

<p align="center">Gregory Fossedal
<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p align="center"><em><u>President</u></em>

<p align="center">Merrick Carey
<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p align="center"><em><u>Vice Presidents</em></u>
<a href="bio.htm">
<p align="center">John Berthoud</a>

<p align="center">John Shanahan
<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p align="center"><em><u>Senior Fellows</u></em>

<p align="center">Loren Thompson

<p align="center">Phil Peters

<p align="center">Paul Steidler
<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p align="center"><em><u>Program Director</u></em>

<p align="center">Don Soifer

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2"><h3 align="center"><font color="#800080"><em><u>Mission</em></font></u></h3>

<p>The Alexis de Tocqueville Institution (AdTI) was founded in 1986 to study, promote, and extend
the principles of classical liberalism: political equality, civil liberty, and economic freedom.

<p>AdTI  conducts research on five key areas of concern to policy makers: 1) education, 2)
immigration, 3) national defense, 4) taxes &amp; economic growth, and 5) deregulation. 
<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2"><h3 align="center"><em><font color="#800080"><u>Accomplishments/Publications</font></em></u></h3>

<p>AdTI publishes numerous studies along with articles and op-eds.  Recent research and writing by
Tocqueville scholars include:

<ul>
  <li>a study of the role of immigrants in patents and inventions in the American economy,</li>
  <li>a study of the impact of immigrants on American cities,</li>
  <li>analysis of the fiscal impact of the legislative agenda of the National Education Association
(NEA),</li>
  <li>analysis of the cost of federal education mandates,</li>
  <li>analysis of PAC activity by the NEA and other major unions,</li>
  <li>assessment of the experience of states with a flat tax,</li>
  <li>assessment of the need for a federal tax cut,</li>
  <li>assessment of trends in the federal work force,</li>
  <li>a study of the 10 Worst Regulations of the federal government,</li>
  <li>analysis of the possibilities for privatization in the Department of Defense.</li>
</ul>

<p>Given the variety and quality of AdTI's activities, it is not surprising that the Institution is getting
more acclaim in the press and the halls of Congress.  AdTI was recently named by <em>The National
Journal</em> as one of five "up-and-coming" think tanks in Washington, D.C.
<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">

