<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#804000" ALINK="#FF8000"><P><A HREF="http://www.schoolreport.com/weacn/news/news.htm"><IMG SRC="http://www.schoolreport.com/weacn/news/toc.gif" WIDTH = 32 HEIGHT = 32 BORDER = 0 ALT="WEACN News"> </A> <A HREF="http://www.schoolreport.com/weacn/index.htm"><IMG SRC="http://www.schoolreport.com/weacn/news/home.gif" WIDTH = 32 HEIGHT = 32 BORDER = 0 ALT="WEACN Home"></A></P>                                                    December 4, 1996<br>Dear interested friends and colleagues, <p>We have come across the following information about the WEA. We thought you might be interested in seeing the comparison of the two sets of figures. <p>Jim Seibert's salary INCREASE ALONE is MORE than a teacher with an M.Ed at the top of salary scale makes in terms of years of experience -including benefits!!  Must be nice to give yourself a raise! He has been under an awful lot of pressure this year from those challengers.....he's probably earned it!! (Just kidding!!) <p>And....it appears in order to afford these raises - they needed to increase the dues by $21.00/year for each member. We have sent an e-mail to members to verify that this raise is a statewide assessment. The previous dues increase was $4,. and the one before that was $12 for the Community Educating monies!! <p>A thought that has crossed our minds is: is this increase to pay for the debt created by the NO! on 177-173 Committee? <p>We can hardly wait until we can see their books!! <p>Our best to each of you! Thanks for all you do!<p>Barb and Cindy<p>1996-97 WEA INFO UPDATE: <br>^bSALARIES AND DUES INCREASE^<p>SALARIES ( BASED ON FIGURES OBTAINED FROM PDC REPORTS)<p>WEA BOARD/LOBBYIST   1995     1996-97  INCREASE<p>JUDITH HARTMAN       $75,635  $78,684  +$3,049<br>ROBERT FISCHER       $85,200           RETIRED<br>KAREN DAVIS          $75,635  NA         <br>ROBERT MAIER         $73,243  $78,684  +$5,443<br>LENORE VEST          $36,96   NA<br>CT PURDOM            $99,120  $120,895  +$21,775<br>LEANN PREILIPP       $81,496  $98,536   +$17,040<br>JAMES SEIBERT        $99,180  $144,832  +$45,712<p>KRISTEEN HANSELMAN <br>(hired for: "NO ON 173-177")   $99,840<br>ROD REGAN<br>(TOOK PLACE OF ROBT. FISHER)   $78,684<p>^bDUES INCREASE INFORMATION^<p>1994-1995 DUES WERE INCREASED BY 12.00  /YR<p>1995-96 DUES WERE INCREASED BY $4.00/YR<p>^b1996-97DUES WERE INCREASED BY $21.00 /YEAR.^<p>^b If every member in Washington state(69,000) was assessed a dues increase of $21/year, then the total increase in income to the WEA coffers this year is: <br>$1,449,000.00!!!!!!!^ 
