<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#804000" ALINK="#FF8000"><P><A HREF="http://www.schoolreport.com/weacn/news/news.htm"><IMG SRC="http://www.schoolreport.com/weacn/news/toc.gif" WIDTH = 32 HEIGHT = 32 BORDER = 0 ALT="WEACN News"> </A> <A HREF="http://www.schoolreport.com/weacn/index.htm"><IMG SRC="http://www.schoolreport.com/weacn/news/home.gif" WIDTH = 32 HEIGHT = 32 BORDER = 0 ALT="WEACN Home"></A></P><br>Dear WEA Challengers,<p>Please send a message to the Attorney General to push for prosecution of the<br>WEA's flagrant crimes against the law, the public's right to fair and free<br>elections, and the constitutional rights of teachers.<p>The Attorney General, Christine Gregoire, may be e mailed at:<p>        emailago@atg.wa.gov<p>Please cc: the message to the Public Disclosure Commission at:<p>        pdc@wln.com<p>The media has helped to raise public awareness of the corruption of the WEA.<br>The WEA, however, is continuing its mantra that this is just a political<br>agenda by a former gubernatorial candidate, Bob Williams, and a conservative<br>think tank, the Evergreen Freedom Foundation.  <p>As teachers, WE must be vigilant in keeping the pressure on.  This fight for<br>justice was initiated by TEACHERS.  There is no conspiracy of organizations<br>trying to bring down the WEA.  This is about Americans--us--fighting for our<br>freedoms.  (Thankfully, we are blessed with the resources and expertise of<br>those who are willing to step out and help us!  Without them, this battle<br>could not have come so far.  Be sure to continue to do your part.) <p>Barb and Cindy<br>WEA Challenger Network <p>P.S.  You might also send a hard copy of your letter to the A.G.  Below is<br>an example of a letter.  Please do not send this exact letter.<br>-------------------------------------------------------------------------------<p>November 21, 1996<p><p>Christine O. Gregoire<br>Washington State Attorney General<br>1125 Washington St. SE<br>P.O. Box 40100<br>Olympia, WA  98504-0100<p>Dear Attorney General Gregoire,<p>As a public school educator, I urge you in the strongest possible terms to<br>prosecute and levy the MAXIMUM penalty possible for the crimes of the<br>Washington Education Association against the teachers and the citizens of<br>our state.<p>I am stunned at WEA's flagrant exploitation of teachers who are breaking<br>their hearts and their backs to educate and nurture the children of our<br>state.  While we work against what seem to be insurmountable odds, the WEA<br>is deceitfully siphoning off money from our paychecks.  The WEA is ruining<br>the reputations and credibility of the honest, hard-working teachers through<br>its corrupt activity. <p>The union is using money that it collects illegally from teachers, and then<br>it is illegally funding candidates and campaigns.  This destroys the<br>public's right to free and fair elections, the essential foundation for the<br>protection of our freedoms. By violating state law and the constitutional<br>rights of teachers, it is making a complete mockery of our democracy.<p>I ask that you prosecute and levy the MAXIMUM penalty allowed by law.  This<br>will discipline the out-of-control union leadership and send a strong<br>message to other political organizations that our rights as teachers and<br>citizens cannot be thwarted by those who hold us in contempt.<p>Thank you for your attention to bringing justice to Washington.  I would<br>appreciate the courtesy of a reply.<p>Sincerely,<p><p>XXXXXXX  XXXXXXXX<br>
<br>
