<P>
WEA Loan to WEA-PAC<BR>
<BR>

<P>
The Life After 134 Task Force recommended that PULSE request a
loan from
<P>
the WEA to cover operational costs and costs identified as PULSE
activities
<P>
which they considered non-political contributions.<BR>

<P>
Nuxoll said that they authorized that a loan could happen after
Initiative
<P>
134 if it were needed.<BR>

<P>
As a way of making sure that we preserved as much of the money
that was
<P>
collected for pure political action to be retained that way. So
I remember
<P>
we talked about what are the things out of this budget that we
used to call
<P>
PULSE that we could now um shall we say lop off or shrink or cut
back move
<P>
so that we could retain as much as possible for the political
