million.

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<ol>
  <li>"NEA supports a mutual, verifiable nuclear freeze with cessation of testing, production, and
further deployment of nuclear delivery systems and other destabilizing systems."</li>
  <ol>
    <li>Cost: -$800 million</li>
    <li>Source:</li>
    <ol>
      <li>HR 790, 103rd Congress, A Bill to Provide for the Termination of Further
Production of Trident II (D-5) missiles.  Cost estimate: -$800 million.</li>
    </ol>
  </ol>
  <li>NEA also "opposes federal funding extending the arms race into outer space."  This can
presumably be interpreted as opposition to the Strategic Defense Initiative.<a href="#N_31_"><sup>(31)</sup></a></li>
  <ol>
    <li>Cost: -$3,800 million</li>
    <li>Source:</li>
    <ol>
      <li>HR 1673, 103rd Congress.  This bill would have limited SDI spending to $1.5
billion per year, a reduction of $2.3 billion.</li>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">    </ol>
  </ol>
